;; Yandex 360 (business mail) DNS records for skazkamuseum.ru — Unisender REMOVED,
;; Yandex is now the only authorized mail sender.
;; Import in Cloudflare: DNS -> Records -> Import and Export -> Import DNS records
;;
;; !! BEFORE importing: delete every Unisender record (see chat guide) — especially
;;    the old SPF TXT and the _dmarc CNAME, otherwise this import creates duplicates
;;    and duplicate SPF/DMARC = broken mail validation.
;; !! If an MX record for mx.yandex.net already exists (from an earlier import),
;;    remove the MX line below before importing, or delete the duplicate after.
;;
;; All records must stay "DNS only" (grey cloud), never proxied.
$ORIGIN skazkamuseum.ru.
$TTL 1800

;; SPF — Yandex only. The include+~all form (not Yandex's redirect= variant) so a
;; second sender can simply be appended later without restructuring the record.
@	1800	IN	TXT	"v=spf1 include:_spf.yandex.net ~all"

;; Mail delivery INTO the Yandex mailboxes (standard Yandex 360 MX)
@	1800	IN	MX	10 mx.yandex.net.

;; DMARC — replaces the deleted Unisender CNAME. p=none = monitor-only, doesn't
;; reject anything; tighten to p=quarantine once mail flow is proven stable.
_dmarc	1800	IN	TXT	"v=DMARC1; p=none;"

;; Yandex's setup wizard will also ask for (add when it shows the values):
;;  - domain ownership TXT:   @  TXT  "yandex-verification=XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX"
;;  - DKIM key:               mail._domainkey  TXT  "v=DKIM1; k=rsa; p=MIGf..."
;; Paste those to Claude and they'll be added here.
